x;y;z\in \mathbb{Z}^+
\left\{\begin{matrix} (xy+1)\vdots z & \\  (xz+1)\vdots y & \\  (yz+1)\vdots x &  \end{matrix}\right.
\left\{\begin{matrix} (xy+1)\vdots z & \\  (xz+1)\vdots y & \\  (yz+1)\vdots x &  \end{matrix}\right.
\Rightarrow \frac{(xy+1)(yz+1)(zx+1)}{xyz}=k(k\in \mathbb{Z})
\Rightarrow(x^2y^2z^2+x^2yz+xyz^2+xy^2z+xy+yz+zx+1)\vdots xyz
\Rightarrow (xy+yz+zx+1)\vdots xyz
\vdots
4\vdots 2
6\vdots 3
202\vdots 101
x \geq y \geq z
 0 \leq xy + yz + zx + 1 < 4xy
z= 1, 2, 3
